description: The Guardian’s picture editors select photographs from around the world
maintext:
Montevideo, Uruguay Alba González, a member of Madres y Familiares de Detenidos Desaparecidos (Mothers and Families of Disappeared Detainees), caresses a portrait of her son as she takes part in a march demanding the identification of the skeletal remains of a woman found last June in a clandestine grave at a military facility near Uruguay’s capital by forensic anthropologists searching for people who disappeared during the 1973-1985 dictatorship
Photograph: Pablo Porciuncula/AFP/Getty Images
title: A rescued orangutan and a festive projection: photos of the day - Thursday
